&lt;p/&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this &quot;java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 0&quot; will happen in the following scenario:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;receiverContexts.size() = 0 at the line 111&lt;br/&gt;
xaResources is created with new XAResource[0]&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;receiverRegistered method is called from other thread between the line 111 and 112&lt;br/&gt;
Now receiverContexts.size() = 1&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As receiverContexts.size() = 1, for-loop is executed&lt;br/&gt;
Then &quot;xaResources[0] = ...&quot; will get ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException at  the line 114 because xaResources is empty array.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
